<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-28T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-28T23:00:00-05:00" n="760" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d760">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">800.0146/219: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-29T11:00:00+07:00">October 29,
                                1943—11 a.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received October 29—8:19 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>2036. Embassy is not informed in regard to discussions between Mountbatten
                        and Chiang (Department’s 1519, October 26) but will make oral inquiry of
                        Stilwell upon latter’s return from India. Stilwell is understood to have
                        been present at the conversations but so far has given us no information
                        thereof.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>